# Conventional Commits format:
# <type>(<scope>): <short description> (max 88 chars)
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation only
#   style    - Formatting, no logic change
#   refactor - Code restructuring, no behavior change
#   perf     - Performance improvement
#   test     - Tests added or updated
#   chore    - Maintenance, dependency updates
#   ci       - CI/CD configuration
#   revert   - Reverting a previous commit
#
# Scope: optional, in snake_case (e.g., feat(altitude_hold): ...)
# Description: imperative mood ("add" not "added"), no period at end
#
# Body (optional — explain WHY, not WHAT):
# Wrap at 72 characters.
#
#
# Footer (optional):
#   Closes #<issue-number>
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#   Co-authored-by: Name <email>
#
# Examples:
#   feat(telemetry): add altitude hold mode
#   fix(serial): correct baud rate initialization
#   docs: update wiring diagram reference
#   chore: update gitleaks to 8.18
